## Authentication

### Two-Legged OAuth (Client Credentials)

For server-to-server integrations using client credentials:

```java
import {{basePackage}}.Client;

Client client = Client.builder()
    .domain("your-institution.blackboard.com")
    .clientId("your-client-id")
    .clientSecret("your-client-secret")
    .build();
```

### Three-Legged OAuth (Authorization Code + PKCE)

For user-delegated access (e.g., acting on behalf of a student or instructor):

```java
import {{basePackage}}.OAuth2Client;

OAuth2Client auth = new OAuth2Client(
    "https://your-institution.blackboard.com",
    "your-client-id",
    "your-client-secret",
    "{{auth.twoLegged.tokenEndpoint}}"
);

// Step 1: Generate the authorization URL with PKCE
OAuth2Client.AuthorizationResult result = auth.getAuthorizationUrl(
    "https://your-app.com/callback",
    "read",    // scope (or null)
    "csrf-tok" // state (or null)
);
// Redirect the user to result.getUrl()
// Store result.getCodeVerifier()

// Step 2: After the user authorizes, exchange the code
auth.exchangeCode(codeFromCallback, "https://your-app.com/callback", result.getCodeVerifier());

// The auth client now holds the user's access token
String token = auth.getToken();
```

## Quick Start

```java
// List courses
var courses = client.courses().list();
System.out.println(courses);

// Get a single course
var course = client.courses().get("externalId:INTRO-101");
System.out.println(course.getName());
```

## Error Handling

```java
import {{basePackage}}.errors.APIError;

try {
    var course = client.courses().get("_invalid_id_");
} catch (APIError e) {
    System.out.println("API error " + e.getStatus() + ": " + e.getMessage());
}
```

## Pagination

Paginated methods return `Iterator`:

```java
var courses = client.courses().listAll();
while (courses.hasNext()) {
    var course = courses.next();
    System.out.println(course.getName());
}
```

